  "title": "OPERATIONS COORDINATOR",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Summary</strong></u></p><p>An Operations Coordinator is responsible for supporting the Operations Team in ensuring smooth vessel operations throughout the fleet.</p><p><u><strong>The Position</strong></u></p><p><strong>Operations Assistant</strong>: This role requires excellent communication and organizational skills, as well as the ability to multitask and work independently.</p><p>Some common duties of an Operations Coordinator may include:</p><p><strong>Operations Assistant Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in updating job schedule on daily basis.</li><li>Provide timely updates and ETA reports of vessel promptly.</li><li>Maintaining an organized filing system, managing records, and updating databases.</li><li>Coordinating with clients and agents to gather the necessary information on vessel updates.</li><li>Maintain close contact with ship agencies for timely updates.</li><li>Assist in any ad-hoc duties, projects, and activities as and when required.</li></ul><p>Overall, an Operations Coordinator should be able to multitask, work independently, and have excellent communication and organizational skills. This role plays a crucial role in the safe and smooth functioning of the operations department.</p>",
